```javascript
const express = require('express');
const router = express.Router();

const transactionController = require('../controllers/transactionController');

// GET /api/transactions
router.get('/', transactionController.getTransactions);

// POST /api/transactions
router.post('/', transactionController.createTransaction);

module.exports = router;
```

In this file, we define the routes for handling GET and POST requests to `/api/transactions`. We import the `transactionController` module and assign the corresponding controller functions to the routes. The `getTransactions` function handles GET requests and the `createTransaction` function handles POST requests. Each route is associated with the respective HTTP method and path.
